1
00:01:31,190 --> 00:01:35,920
[Life Is a Choice]

2
00:01:36,350 --> 00:01:38,950
Lin Xi, It's me, Gu Nian!

3
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:38,580
[Episode 2]

4
00:01:39,479 --> 00:01:39,870
Look.

5
00:01:41,509 --> 00:01:42,750
I really am Gu Nian.

6
00:01:43,900 --> 00:01:45,110
I can't go back.

7
00:01:45,470 --> 00:01:46,470
In my timeline,

8
00:01:46,500 --> 00:01:47,950
I might already be dead.

9
00:01:48,410 --> 00:01:50,000
I had no choice but to come to you.

10
00:01:50,150 --> 00:01:50,820
Dude,

11
00:01:51,509 --> 00:01:52,550
I'm a doctor.

12
00:01:52,750 --> 00:01:54,460
I believe in science, okay?

13
00:01:54,780 --> 00:01:55,580
How can you...

14
00:01:56,020 --> 00:01:58,340
[Do you believe there's another you in this world?]

15
00:01:58,820 --> 00:02:00,310
I've done all the tests.

16
00:02:00,430 --> 00:02:02,230
All the psychiatrists said there's nothing wrong with me.

17
00:02:02,260 --> 00:02:03,450
This is the truth.

18
00:02:03,490 --> 00:02:04,930
This is science.

19
00:02:05,250 --> 00:02:06,990
This is a repeatedly verified truth.

20
00:02:07,070 --> 00:02:08,669
You need to look beyond the surface and see the essence.

21
00:02:08,699 --> 00:02:10,430
The essence I see

22
00:02:10,630 --> 00:02:12,030
is you using such a despicable method

23
00:02:12,030 --> 00:02:13,150
to get girls' attention

24
00:02:13,320 --> 00:02:14,760
and waste medical resources.

25
00:02:14,760 --> 00:02:16,520
I'm off work now. Get out.

26
00:02:18,920 --> 00:02:19,280
I'll leave.

27
00:02:20,530 --> 00:02:21,210
Lin Xi.

28
00:02:22,320 --> 00:02:23,230
Keep your distance.

29
00:02:25,490 --> 00:02:26,760
Listen to me carefully.

30
00:02:27,130 --> 00:02:28,160
You're three years older than me.

31
00:02:28,160 --> 00:02:29,040
We grew up together.

32
00:02:29,040 --> 00:02:31,040
You celebrated every one of my birthdays.

33
00:02:31,430 --> 00:02:33,040
When we were little, after my dad passed away,

34
00:02:33,040 --> 00:02:35,170
I lived at your house for a long time.

35
00:02:35,610 --> 00:02:36,440
Once,

36
00:02:36,440 --> 00:02:38,050
I accidentally broke a vase at your house

37
00:02:38,160 --> 00:02:39,800
and found your dad's secret savings,

38
00:02:39,940 --> 00:02:41,300
which is when I found out your dad was having an affair.

39
00:02:41,610 --> 00:02:43,550
From then on, you no longer believed in love.

40
00:02:43,850 --> 00:02:45,410
You swore you'd never choose marriage in this lifetime

41
00:02:45,410 --> 00:02:46,290
and would dedicate yourself to medicine forever...

42
00:02:46,290 --> 00:02:46,930
Shut up!

43
00:02:50,690 --> 00:02:52,079
Gu Nian would never use these old scars

44
00:02:52,079 --> 00:02:53,450
to hurt me again.

45
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:55,530
I don't care where you got this information,

46
00:02:55,770 --> 00:02:56,680
but I'm warning you,

47
00:02:57,340 --> 00:02:58,620
if you dare to harass me again,

48
00:02:58,960 --> 00:02:59,840
I'll call the police and have you arrested.

49
00:03:02,720 --> 00:03:03,400
Move aside.

50
00:03:07,320 --> 00:03:08,000
Keep moving.

51
00:03:16,130 --> 00:03:17,890
Lin Xi, I really am Gu Nian.

52
00:03:17,890 --> 00:03:18,770
Please believe me.

53
00:03:35,050 --> 00:03:35,720
Is it all?

54
00:03:35,740 --> 00:03:36,400
It's all.

55
00:03:36,930 --> 00:03:38,220
I told you to bring some nice clothes

56
00:03:38,250 --> 00:03:38,690
for me.

57
00:03:38,690 --> 00:03:40,610
I usually wear just these few colors.

58
00:03:41,770 --> 00:03:43,640
The people majoring in Computer Science have really terrible taste.

59
00:03:46,700 --> 00:03:48,410
They look pretty nice to me.

60
00:04:00,370 --> 00:04:00,960
Gao...

61
00:04:02,450 --> 00:04:03,120
Gao Ren.

62
00:04:03,280 --> 00:04:06,000
Do you know what spatial computing is?

63
00:04:06,260 --> 00:04:07,020
What's that?

64
00:04:07,120 --> 00:04:07,730
It's...

65
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:09,320
Have you ever seen a device that,

66
00:04:09,320 --> 00:04:10,250
when worn on your face,

67
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:11,370
puts you into a multidimensional space

68
00:04:11,370 --> 00:04:12,830
where you can have immersive conversations?

69
00:04:12,830 --> 00:04:13,960
And you can also use this device

70
00:04:13,960 --> 00:04:15,330
as a medium to open a wormhole

71
00:04:15,330 --> 00:04:16,810
to another time and place,

72
00:04:16,850 --> 00:04:18,240
and then open a multidimensional space-time.

73
00:04:18,310 --> 00:04:19,440
Multidimensional space-time, do you know what it is?

74
00:04:20,100 --> 00:04:20,890
Boss,

75
00:04:21,149 --> 00:04:23,060
this idea is amazing.

76
00:04:23,370 --> 00:04:24,520
If you successfully invent this thing,

77
00:04:24,520 --> 00:04:26,530
you will make history.

78
00:04:26,850 --> 00:04:27,840
It hasn't been invented yet?

79
00:04:27,840 --> 00:04:29,050
Of course not.

80
00:04:30,090 --> 00:04:30,880
Don't worry,

81
00:04:31,120 --> 00:04:33,370
I won't tell anyone about this.

82
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:36,390
The technology hasn't developed to that point yet?

83
00:04:36,730 --> 00:04:37,460
Oh, no.

84
00:04:37,490 --> 00:04:38,530
I really can't go back.

85
00:04:40,550 --> 00:04:41,880
Do you know any way to make someone believe

86
00:04:41,880 --> 00:04:43,320
that there's another version of herself

87
00:04:43,320 --> 00:04:45,370
from the future in this world?

88
00:04:46,330 --> 00:04:47,720
There might be a way,

89
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:49,680
But I guess she'd have to take a hit on the head

90
00:04:49,880 --> 00:04:51,240
like you did.

91
00:04:51,480 --> 00:04:52,560
Think about it,

92
00:04:52,930 --> 00:04:55,960
when Newton got hit by the apple, he had an epiphany.

93
00:04:55,980 --> 00:04:58,020
You got hit by a helmet, and your head got cracked open.

94
00:04:59,890 --> 00:05:03,000
Does external force really help brain development?

95
00:05:04,110 --> 00:05:05,430
Forget it, I'll figure it out myself.

96
00:05:11,700 --> 00:05:13,190
Do you know my phone password?

97
00:05:13,850 --> 00:05:14,760
I don't know.

98
00:05:23,010 --> 00:05:24,650
Why isn't there a fingerprint unlock?

99
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:26,480
Didn't you tell us

100
00:05:26,510 --> 00:05:27,910
that thing is not safe?

101
00:05:30,050 --> 00:05:31,130
Do you have any cash?

102
00:05:31,170 --> 00:05:33,610
No, you still haven't paid me back for your hospital fee.

103
00:05:34,330 --> 00:05:35,210
As you can see,

104
00:05:35,210 --> 00:05:36,090
I can't unlock my phone right now,

105
00:05:36,090 --> 00:05:37,310
so I can't use mobile payment.

106
00:05:37,590 --> 00:05:38,800
Just lend me some cash.

107
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:40,370
I really don't have much left.

108
00:05:40,370 --> 00:05:42,080
Ask your family for it.

109
00:05:42,159 --> 00:05:43,520
Then it means you still have some.

110
00:05:43,550 --> 00:05:44,570
Come on, lend me some.

111
00:05:47,970 --> 00:05:48,800
This is all I have.

112
00:05:49,030 --> 00:05:50,310
Record it. I'll pay you back.

113
00:05:59,880 --> 00:06:01,930
Gao Ren, you must have more.

114
00:06:03,140 --> 00:06:03,970
I really don't.

115
00:06:04,180 --> 00:06:05,360
You're lying to me, aren't you?

116
00:06:05,520 --> 00:06:06,130
I'm not.

117
00:06:07,480 --> 00:06:08,090
You must have more.

118
00:06:08,280 --> 00:06:09,000
I don't.

119
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:09,680
Take it out.

120
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:14,320
It's the last bit.

121
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:15,640
I'm your boss.

122
00:06:15,640 --> 00:06:16,720
Don't you trust me?

123
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:17,930
Boss,

124
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:19,280
you've changed.

125
00:06:21,320 --> 00:06:22,970
Here, for food and the taxi.

126
00:06:24,870 --> 00:06:26,950
Remember to call me at 8 PM.

127
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:31,360
Wait, where are you going?

128
00:06:31,680 --> 00:06:32,970
Don't forget, 8 PM.

129
00:06:38,130 --> 00:06:40,720
Five yuan for taxi and food?

130
00:06:46,650 --> 00:06:48,610
[The relationship between time travelers and crazy people]

131
00:06:51,270 --> 00:06:53,790
[Time travelers]

132
00:06:57,480 --> 00:07:02,780
[Crazy people]

133
00:07:03,480 --> 00:07:04,570
The number one shero of the CCYL Committee.

134
00:07:06,390 --> 00:07:07,240
President?

135
00:07:08,000 --> 00:07:09,110
Thank you for today.

136
00:07:09,530 --> 00:07:11,290
You stepped in when I needed help.

137
00:07:12,770 --> 00:07:13,690
You left your helmet at the theater.

138
00:07:13,690 --> 00:07:14,570
I've been looking for you for a while.

139
00:07:14,760 --> 00:07:17,280
Every time I lose something, I forget about it.

140
00:07:17,280 --> 00:07:18,160
Thank you, President.

141
00:07:22,010 --> 00:07:23,650
This motorcycle is quite nice.

142
00:07:24,770 --> 00:07:26,260
The color scheme is so cool.

143
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:27,980
It suits you perfectly.

144
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:31,090
Wait, President, your face...

145
00:07:31,780 --> 00:07:32,580
My...

146
00:07:33,060 --> 00:07:35,280
It's nothing, not worth mentioning.

147
00:07:39,850 --> 00:07:40,820
I guess I was just unlucky

148
00:07:41,090 --> 00:07:42,320
running into that crazy person.

149
00:07:43,320 --> 00:07:45,180
Do you have time now?

150
00:07:45,930 --> 00:07:46,760
To express my gratitude,

151
00:07:46,760 --> 00:07:47,930
I want to treat you to a meal.

152
00:07:48,460 --> 00:07:49,180
Yes, I do.

153
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:50,520
Where should we go?

154
00:07:50,520 --> 00:07:51,360
How about...

155
00:07:52,540 --> 00:07:53,120
Is that okay?

156
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:55,440
I know a really good restaurant.

157
00:07:55,440 --> 00:07:56,290
It's not far from here.

158
00:07:56,530 --> 00:07:57,440
I'll drive you there.

159
00:07:57,890 --> 00:07:58,510
Let's go.

160
00:08:00,830 --> 00:08:02,740
Do I just snap it on directly?

161
00:08:03,180 --> 00:08:03,940
Yes.

162
00:08:10,280 --> 00:08:11,720
Can... can this hold my weight?

163
00:08:11,720 --> 00:08:12,520
Get on.

164
00:08:19,730 --> 00:08:20,490
Are you ready?

165
00:08:20,490 --> 00:08:22,600
Yes. I can't see anything now.

166
00:08:22,600 --> 00:08:23,840
This is my first time on a motorcycle.

167
00:08:24,160 --> 00:08:25,890
It's just right.

168
00:08:26,500 --> 00:08:28,020
Gu Nian, Gu Nian.

169
00:08:32,400 --> 00:08:33,280
Gu Nian!

170
00:08:34,010 --> 00:08:34,850
Gu Nian!

171
00:08:34,890 --> 00:08:35,940
Gu Nian!

172
00:08:36,039 --> 00:08:36,799
Gu Nian!

173
00:08:37,210 --> 00:08:38,090
Gu Nian!

174
00:08:39,210 --> 00:08:40,080
Gu Nian!

175
00:08:40,409 --> 00:08:41,289
Gu Nian!

176
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:43,080
Gu Nian!

177
00:08:54,610 --> 00:08:55,200
Hello?

178
00:08:55,580 --> 00:08:56,180
Gu Nian,

179
00:08:56,200 --> 00:08:57,720
you didn't take Feng Huanan to the cafeteria,

180
00:08:57,750 --> 00:08:58,370
but where did you go?

181
00:08:58,370 --> 00:08:59,890
Is this guy crazy?

182
00:09:04,960 --> 00:09:06,000
Gu Nian.

183
00:09:08,560 --> 00:09:09,560
Over here.

184
00:09:11,450 --> 00:09:14,250
Who is being treated to a meal here?

185
00:09:14,270 --> 00:09:15,630
Why did you have to call me over?

186
00:09:15,850 --> 00:09:16,680
I'm telling you,

187
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:18,870
it's the big talent from the economics department,

188
00:09:18,960 --> 00:09:20,760
the president of our drama club, Feng Huanan.

189
00:09:21,690 --> 00:09:22,370
I know him.

190
00:09:22,390 --> 00:09:25,540
He's the male lead in that legendary love story,

191
00:09:25,560 --> 00:09:26,230
right?

192
00:09:26,420 --> 00:09:27,570
Don't say anything reckless.

193
00:09:27,820 --> 00:09:28,590
You know what?

194
00:09:28,760 --> 00:09:29,850
He broke up,

195
00:09:29,870 --> 00:09:32,270
and today he got beaten up for no reason.

196
00:09:32,300 --> 00:09:33,410
Don't make things worse.

197
00:09:34,570 --> 00:09:35,410
Alright, alright.

198
00:09:35,410 --> 00:09:37,450
The male lead has turned into a fallen prince, right?

199
00:09:39,390 --> 00:09:40,190
Where is he?

200
00:09:40,770 --> 00:09:41,880
He went to the bathroom.

201
00:09:42,960 --> 00:09:44,480
You came back last night?

202
00:09:44,480 --> 00:09:45,960
I thought you didn't come back.

203
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:47,440
If I had known, I would have brought you along.

204
00:09:48,210 --> 00:09:49,110
Don't even mention it.

205
00:09:49,110 --> 00:09:50,960
I thought I'd be able to come back earlier,

206
00:09:50,960 --> 00:09:52,560
but those people can really drink.

207
00:09:52,560 --> 00:09:53,570
They drank all the way until morning.

208
00:09:53,690 --> 00:09:55,290
But they were quite generous.

209
00:09:55,610 --> 00:09:56,250
Look.

210
00:09:57,140 --> 00:09:58,220
Do you remember this dress?

211
00:09:59,480 --> 00:10:01,490
Isn't this the dress you didn't buy last time when we went shopping together

212
00:10:01,490 --> 00:10:02,560
because you thought it was too expensive?

213
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:03,880
Yeah, I bought it.

214
00:10:06,690 --> 00:10:07,480
Come on, Tu.

215
00:10:07,920 --> 00:10:09,770
I don't think this is a long-term solution.

216
00:10:10,120 --> 00:10:11,330
Have you thought about changing jobs?

217
00:10:12,040 --> 00:10:12,760
You don't know.

218
00:10:12,760 --> 00:10:14,810
Working at the KTV is just a stepping stone for me.

219
00:10:15,000 --> 00:10:16,440
Once I save enough money,

220
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:18,280
I'll learn to play golf

221
00:10:18,280 --> 00:10:19,650
and become a caddy.

222
00:10:19,770 --> 00:10:21,040
It's all about moving up step by step.

223
00:10:21,900 --> 00:10:22,700
Can I eat?

224
00:10:22,740 --> 00:10:23,410
I'm starving.

225
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:24,870
Wait a second. It's impolite.

226
00:10:25,220 --> 00:10:26,340
Have some water.

227
00:10:27,270 --> 00:10:28,630
You're really

228
00:10:29,230 --> 00:10:31,030
a heartless woman.

229
00:10:31,240 --> 00:10:32,120
Come on.

230
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:36,800
Well, Nan, let me introduce you.

231
00:10:37,110 --> 00:10:38,990
This is my best friend

232
00:10:39,030 --> 00:10:40,260
and roommate, Lyu Tu.

233
00:10:40,450 --> 00:10:41,370
And this is

234
00:10:41,370 --> 00:10:43,720
our drama club president, Feng Huanan.

235
00:10:44,350 --> 00:10:45,020
Nice to meet you.

236
00:10:45,670 --> 00:10:46,340
Nice to meet you.

237
00:10:47,650 --> 00:10:50,080
Nan, thanks for getting my helmet back.

238
00:10:50,300 --> 00:10:51,480
I'll treat you to this meal today.

239
00:10:51,620 --> 00:10:52,530
How can that be?

240
00:10:52,560 --> 00:10:54,040
How can I let a girl pay?

241
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:01,870
Thanks, miss.

242
00:11:05,160 --> 00:11:06,400
What's wrong? Who is it?

243
00:11:06,400 --> 00:11:08,120
The lunatic who hit you this morning.

244
00:11:08,120 --> 00:11:09,090
He keeps calling me.

245
00:11:09,090 --> 00:11:09,970
Is he crazy?

246
00:11:10,050 --> 00:11:11,320
Oh my, now that you mention it,

247
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:13,080
I should definitely treat you.

248
00:11:13,080 --> 00:11:14,250
You helped me so much.

249
00:11:14,540 --> 00:11:17,120
We can't let someone who just broke up treat us.

250
00:11:19,800 --> 00:11:21,410
Come on. Is my little matter

251
00:11:21,570 --> 00:11:23,130
really that big of a deal?

252
00:11:23,430 --> 00:11:24,660
About your little matter,

253
00:11:24,930 --> 00:11:27,690
I've already heard three versions of it.

254
00:11:27,710 --> 00:11:28,910
So the truth

255
00:11:29,130 --> 00:11:29,920
has to come from you,

256
00:11:30,090 --> 00:11:31,490
the person involved.

257
00:11:32,550 --> 00:11:33,360
I'm telling you,

258
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:35,760
the truth is usually the most boring version.

259
00:11:36,180 --> 00:11:38,410
Sometimes, you want to be with someone forever,

260
00:11:38,850 --> 00:11:40,130
but the other person might not feel the same way.

261
00:11:40,890 --> 00:11:42,040
Why does it sound like

262
00:11:42,290 --> 00:11:44,170
your ex is a bit of a player?

263
00:11:45,390 --> 00:11:46,270
It's not that.

264
00:11:46,690 --> 00:11:48,200
It's just that we want different things.

265
00:11:48,280 --> 00:11:49,200
Everyone has their own aspirations.

266
00:11:49,520 --> 00:11:51,330
So what's up with your face?

267
00:11:51,650 --> 00:11:52,240
This?

268
00:11:52,770 --> 00:11:54,570
It's all thanks to that crazy person.

269
00:11:55,830 --> 00:11:56,550
Well,

270
00:11:56,730 --> 00:11:57,940
I'm going out for a bit.

271
00:11:58,290 --> 00:11:59,930
Where are you going? We're eating.

272
00:12:01,220 --> 00:12:01,850
Wait for me.

273
00:12:01,890 --> 00:12:02,540
Come back soon.

274
00:12:10,880 --> 00:12:11,960
You guys ordered all this?

275
00:12:12,160 --> 00:12:12,770
Yeah.

276
00:12:13,190 --> 00:12:15,070
These are the dishes that Nian and I love the most.

277
00:12:16,820 --> 00:12:19,660
It's good. You guys have a good appetite.

278
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:35,170
Xi, you're back.

279
00:12:35,820 --> 00:12:36,820
Put the knife down!

280
00:12:36,850 --> 00:12:38,420
How do you know where I live? Stop!

281
00:12:39,540 --> 00:12:40,660
These are scissors.

282
00:12:40,690 --> 00:12:42,240
Of course I know you live here.

283
00:12:42,540 --> 00:12:43,260
Have you forgotten?

284
00:12:43,280 --> 00:12:45,400
I accompanied you to meet several real estate agents back then.

285
00:12:45,620 --> 00:12:47,340
Only this house was available for full rent and wasn't facing a street.

286
00:12:47,890 --> 00:12:49,360
What exactly do you want?

287
00:12:49,360 --> 00:12:50,530
It's not on the first floor, so it has no bad smells.

288
00:12:50,550 --> 00:12:51,970
It's not on the top floor, so there's no risk of leaks.

289
00:12:52,010 --> 00:12:53,680
The bathroom has separate dry and wet areas, so the shower is independent.

290
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:55,490
If it weren't for the homeowner's urgent need to go abroad

291
00:12:55,490 --> 00:12:56,520
to take care of her elderly mother,

292
00:12:56,580 --> 00:12:57,890
you wouldn't have stumbled upon this bargain.

293
00:13:01,920 --> 00:13:03,650
You didn't install surveillance in my house, did you?

294
00:13:03,970 --> 00:13:05,960
Xi, we live in a socialist society

295
00:13:05,960 --> 00:13:06,930
and grew up in a time of peace and prosperity.

296
00:13:06,930 --> 00:13:08,570
Believing in science is the right thing to do.

297
00:13:09,250 --> 00:13:10,770
But it happened.

298
00:13:11,150 --> 00:13:12,440
I don't know why.

299
00:13:12,610 --> 00:13:13,380
Although it's shocking,

300
00:13:13,450 --> 00:13:14,670
it might not be a bad surprise.

301
00:13:14,870 --> 00:13:15,410
Don't you

302
00:13:15,410 --> 00:13:17,050
want Gu Nian to live a happy life

303
00:13:17,190 --> 00:13:18,600
under the guidance of a sage?

304
00:13:18,630 --> 00:13:20,030
You can consider me a sage if you want.

305
00:13:20,280 --> 00:13:21,520
What are you talking about? What sage?

306
00:13:21,520 --> 00:13:21,920
I don't understand.

307
00:13:21,920 --> 00:13:22,720
I'm telling you,

308
00:13:22,740 --> 00:13:23,800
if you don't explain clearly

309
00:13:23,800 --> 00:13:25,000
how you know the situation of my house,

310
00:13:25,480 --> 00:13:26,410
I'll call the police right away.

311
00:13:28,120 --> 00:13:30,050
Gu Nian. I am Gu Nian.

312
00:13:30,080 --> 00:13:31,130
I really am Gu Nian.

313
00:13:34,410 --> 00:13:35,090
What?

314
00:13:35,920 --> 00:13:37,360
Lin Xi, don't, don't call the police.

315
00:13:37,360 --> 00:13:38,210
Lin Xi, don't. I'm Gu Nian.

316
00:13:38,210 --> 00:13:38,850
What are you doing?

317
00:13:38,850 --> 00:13:39,880
I really am Gu Nian!

318
00:13:40,370 --> 00:13:41,760
Lunatic! Let go of me!

319
00:13:42,250 --> 00:13:42,880
Do you remember

320
00:13:42,880 --> 00:13:44,720
the band-aid we used when we played pretend as kids?

321
00:13:48,770 --> 00:13:51,290
Look. When we were kids playing pretend,

322
00:13:51,290 --> 00:13:52,640
you were the doctor, and I was the patient.

323
00:13:52,880 --> 00:13:54,640
You stuck the band-aid on my head,

324
00:13:55,110 --> 00:13:56,180
and we couldn't get it off.

325
00:13:56,220 --> 00:13:57,230
I had to cut my hair short.

326
00:13:57,380 --> 00:13:58,280
Do you remember that?

327
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:03,920
Dr. Lin, you're off work?

328
00:14:04,690 --> 00:14:05,930
Are you dating?

329
00:14:06,280 --> 00:14:07,890
This young man seems really nice.

330
00:14:08,650 --> 00:14:10,090
You young people don't like cooking.

331
00:14:10,090 --> 00:14:11,360
Why don't you come and eat at my place?

332
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:12,970
Sure.

333
00:14:14,560 --> 00:14:15,760
Carry the vegetables for her.

334
00:14:15,930 --> 00:14:16,620
Let me do it.

335
00:14:17,610 --> 00:14:18,720
Smooth, young man.

336
00:14:19,080 --> 00:14:21,400
I'll make you stir-fried vegetables and braised pork.

337
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:21,920
Okay.

338
00:14:21,920 --> 00:14:22,560
They're delicious.

339
00:14:22,560 --> 00:14:23,850
I haven't eaten today.

340
00:14:23,850 --> 00:14:25,080
I guarantee you'll have two more bowls of rice.

341
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:25,880
Sure thing.

342
00:14:27,070 --> 00:14:28,800
Ma'am, I'm not going.

343
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:31,360
Aren't you going to have the braised pork?

344
00:14:34,160 --> 00:14:34,800
Lin Xi,

345
00:14:34,970 --> 00:14:36,050
I'll definitely find Gu Nian

346
00:14:36,050 --> 00:14:36,760
and get her a new husband

347
00:14:36,760 --> 00:14:38,120
and a new life.

348
00:14:39,640 --> 00:14:40,570
What are you doing?

349
00:14:40,890 --> 00:14:41,840
If you don't go out now, I'll call the police.

350
00:14:41,840 --> 00:14:42,330
I'm warning you.

351
00:14:42,330 --> 00:14:43,330
Get out of here right now!

352
00:14:43,330 --> 00:14:44,010
Xi, look!

353
00:14:44,530 --> 00:14:45,480
They're from your graduation trip.

354
00:14:45,540 --> 00:14:47,100
I took these two for you.

355
00:14:47,680 --> 00:14:48,410
There's more.

356
00:14:50,590 --> 00:14:52,080
Where's the box? Did you throw it away?

357
00:14:53,200 --> 00:14:54,650
What box?

358
00:14:55,090 --> 00:14:56,280
The white box.

359
00:14:56,280 --> 00:14:57,540
The one we made together when we were kids.

360
00:15:05,960 --> 00:15:07,690
There it is. You really didn't throw it away.

361
00:15:12,560 --> 00:15:14,200
This one was made by you.

362
00:15:15,810 --> 00:15:17,880
And you gave this one to me.

363
00:15:18,890 --> 00:15:19,850
Do you remember?

364
00:15:20,160 --> 00:15:21,440
When you were in fourth grade,

365
00:15:21,670 --> 00:15:22,880
I played in the mud in a skirt,

366
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:23,880
came home late,

367
00:15:23,880 --> 00:15:24,840
and got beaten by my dad.

368
00:15:25,080 --> 00:15:26,250
And you argued with your mom

369
00:15:26,250 --> 00:15:27,160
because you did poorly on an exam.

370
00:15:27,410 --> 00:15:29,010
We promised each other to run away from home together.

371
00:15:29,720 --> 00:15:30,800
That night, I waited for you

372
00:15:30,800 --> 00:15:31,530
under the slide all night,

373
00:15:31,530 --> 00:15:32,360
but you didn't show up.

374
00:15:32,680 --> 00:15:34,050
The next day, you told me that

375
00:15:34,050 --> 00:15:35,400
you actually forgot about our plan to run away

376
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:37,010
because of two Olympiad math problems.

377
00:15:37,470 --> 00:15:40,390
You still remember such a thing?

378
00:15:40,430 --> 00:15:41,750
Of course I remember.

379
00:15:42,240 --> 00:15:43,970
I got bitten by mosquitoes all night long.

380
00:16:04,130 --> 00:16:04,860
You...

381
00:16:06,860 --> 00:16:08,010
really are Gu Nian?

382
00:16:10,640 --> 00:16:12,070
Gu Nian from seven years later?

383
00:16:12,730 --> 00:16:13,740
Lin Xi!

384
00:16:20,060 --> 00:16:21,720
I've missed you so much.

385
00:16:24,520 --> 00:16:25,880
What's wrong with you?

386
00:16:25,880 --> 00:16:27,160
The waiter was carrying it just fine.

387
00:16:27,160 --> 00:16:28,560
Why did you have to grab it?

388
00:16:28,560 --> 00:16:29,680
Why weren't you more careful?

389
00:16:29,680 --> 00:16:31,360
Look at my dress. I just bought it today.

390
00:16:31,360 --> 00:16:32,080
I thought he couldn't carry that many dishes.

391
00:16:32,080 --> 00:16:33,110
I was just trying to help.

392
00:16:33,110 --> 00:16:35,480
Help? But you spilled it all over me.

393
00:16:35,630 --> 00:16:37,710
Here, use my clothes to cover it up for now.

394
00:16:37,740 --> 00:16:39,480
What good can your clothes do?

395
00:16:40,360 --> 00:16:41,640
Wait, what's going on here?

396
00:16:41,640 --> 00:16:42,730
Did you spill food on yourself?

397
00:16:42,770 --> 00:16:43,730
On myself?

398
00:16:43,740 --> 00:16:45,420
He spilled it.

399
00:16:46,480 --> 00:16:48,480
It's okay, I'll take it to the dry cleaners.

400
00:16:48,480 --> 00:16:49,560
They can definitely get it clean.

401
00:16:49,650 --> 00:16:51,730
I saved up for a whole month to buy this,

402
00:16:51,730 --> 00:16:53,180
and now it's ruined.

403
00:16:53,560 --> 00:16:54,370
Don't be so loud.

404
00:16:54,370 --> 00:16:55,640
Why are you giving him such a hard time?

405
00:16:55,980 --> 00:16:57,060
I'll buy you a new one.

406
00:16:57,320 --> 00:16:58,840
No way. Why should you buy it?

407
00:16:58,950 --> 00:16:59,920
Whoever made it dirty should be the one to do it.

408
00:17:00,240 --> 00:17:00,960
Fine,

409
00:17:01,330 --> 00:17:01,840
I'll compensate you.

410
00:17:02,280 --> 00:17:03,680
Add me on WeChat right now,

411
00:17:03,870 --> 00:17:04,730
so you don't run away later.

412
00:17:05,089 --> 00:17:05,560
Don't worry,

413
00:17:05,560 --> 00:17:06,369
I won't run away.

414
00:17:06,680 --> 00:17:07,690
Just tell me how much it costs,

415
00:17:07,690 --> 00:17:08,400
and I'll pay you back.

416
00:17:08,569 --> 00:17:10,250
I want cash, cash only.

417
00:17:10,359 --> 00:17:11,680
Okay, no problem.

418
00:17:13,119 --> 00:17:14,089
What are you doing?

419
00:17:14,089 --> 00:17:14,680
Shush.

420
00:17:14,680 --> 00:17:15,800
There's no need for this.

421
00:17:16,240 --> 00:17:17,050
Gu Nian,

422
00:17:17,490 --> 00:17:18,280
I have something to do.

423
00:17:18,280 --> 00:17:19,000
I'll be leaving now.

424
00:17:19,319 --> 00:17:20,079
Pay the bill.

425
00:17:20,319 --> 00:17:21,890
I've already paid.

426
00:17:26,260 --> 00:17:26,950
Wait.

427
00:17:27,750 --> 00:17:29,120
Sit down and have something to eat first.

428
00:17:29,120 --> 00:17:29,640
Have something to eat first.

429
00:17:29,640 --> 00:17:30,370
Where are you going?

430
00:17:30,370 --> 00:17:31,280
Wait for me, wait for me.

431
00:17:31,990 --> 00:17:33,390
Nan, Nan.

432
00:17:33,810 --> 00:17:35,680
Nan, don't be angry.

433
00:17:35,680 --> 00:17:37,730
My friend was just kidding.

434
00:17:38,020 --> 00:17:41,160
I just went out and bought some medicine for you.

435
00:17:41,490 --> 00:17:43,090
Medicine? What medicine?

436
00:17:43,340 --> 00:17:45,850
Didn't you get hit in the face today?

437
00:17:46,090 --> 00:17:47,650
I bought you some medicine.

438
00:17:50,360 --> 00:17:52,440
You stepped in to save me,

439
00:17:53,120 --> 00:17:54,570
and then bought me medicine.

440
00:17:55,760 --> 00:17:56,770
I feel embarrassed.

441
00:17:57,890 --> 00:17:59,680
But the way you handle things

442
00:18:00,650 --> 00:18:02,170
doesn't really match the Gu Nian in the rumors.

443
00:18:02,930 --> 00:18:04,250
What's Gu Nian like in the rumors?

444
00:18:04,620 --> 00:18:06,780
A tomboy or a tough guy?

445
00:18:09,160 --> 00:18:10,090
Oh, right.

446
00:18:10,090 --> 00:18:12,660
I actually went to the drama club to find you today

447
00:18:12,690 --> 00:18:13,640
for something important.

448
00:18:13,980 --> 00:18:14,730
The list

449
00:18:14,730 --> 00:18:16,880
for last year's financial aid just came out,

450
00:18:16,880 --> 00:18:18,080
and your name is on it.

451
00:18:18,080 --> 00:18:19,720
The teacher asked me to get your signature.

452
00:18:19,720 --> 00:18:21,840
But with everything that happened today, I forgot about it.

453
00:18:22,650 --> 00:18:23,290
Financial aid?

454
00:18:24,110 --> 00:18:25,120
I don't need it now.

455
00:18:25,320 --> 00:18:26,760
I'm about to graduate,

456
00:18:27,040 --> 00:18:28,880
so the financial aid should go to someone who needs it more.

457
00:18:29,150 --> 00:18:29,930
Why?

458
00:18:29,930 --> 00:18:31,210
Your name is on the list.

459
00:18:31,210 --> 00:18:32,240
Why don't you want it?

460
00:18:33,850 --> 00:18:35,210
If I take it,

461
00:18:35,370 --> 00:18:37,340
it'll make it look like I didn't make any progress

462
00:18:37,660 --> 00:18:38,820
during these four years of college.

463
00:18:39,180 --> 00:18:39,660
Right?

464
00:18:40,980 --> 00:18:43,300
Alright then. Just keep the medicine.

465
00:18:44,330 --> 00:18:45,050
Okay.

466
00:18:46,210 --> 00:18:48,240
I'll respectfully comply then.

467
00:18:48,270 --> 00:18:48,980
Thank you.

468
00:18:49,820 --> 00:18:52,530
How's your wrist? Is it better?

469
00:18:53,550 --> 00:18:54,870
It's nothing serious.

470
00:18:55,160 --> 00:18:55,680
Oh, by the way,

471
00:18:55,680 --> 00:18:57,530
why didn't I see you at the hospital today?

472
00:18:57,770 --> 00:18:59,490
It's just a small injury, nothing serious,

473
00:18:59,500 --> 00:19:00,550
so I didn't go to the hospital.

474
00:19:01,340 --> 00:19:03,590
By the way, who was that crazy person?

475
00:19:03,690 --> 00:19:05,040
I got beaten up for no reason.

476
00:19:05,040 --> 00:19:05,570
I need to find a chance

477
00:19:05,570 --> 00:19:06,360
to get back at him.

478
00:19:06,430 --> 00:19:07,330
You'd better not.

479
00:19:07,450 --> 00:19:09,760
I think that guy definitely has some mental issues.

480
00:19:09,760 --> 00:19:10,560
Don't mess with people like that.

481
00:19:12,620 --> 00:19:13,490
Lin Xi.

482
00:19:14,420 --> 00:19:15,230
What?

483
00:19:16,080 --> 00:19:17,130
I'm leaving now.

484
00:19:17,940 --> 00:19:19,300
Okay, okay. I'll be right there.

485
00:19:20,840 --> 00:19:21,800
My purse!

486
00:19:21,830 --> 00:19:22,500
My purse!

487
00:19:22,690 --> 00:19:23,380
What's wrong?

488
00:19:23,410 --> 00:19:24,250
Keep eating.

489
00:19:25,250 --> 00:19:26,410
Wait, you're leaving?

490
00:19:27,130 --> 00:19:27,960
You're not eating?

491
00:19:29,890 --> 00:19:31,690
But we ordered so much.

492
00:20:08,090 --> 00:20:09,170
Lin Xi!

493
00:20:10,950 --> 00:20:11,930
What's going on?

494
00:20:12,370 --> 00:20:13,250
I'll call an ambulance.

495
00:20:13,720 --> 00:20:14,800
I've already called.

496
00:20:14,800 --> 00:20:16,330
Come on. What's wrong with him?

497
00:20:16,330 --> 00:20:17,920
He doesn't want to live anymore. He wants to die.

498
00:20:17,920 --> 00:20:19,240
He just took sleeping pills.

499
00:20:19,240 --> 00:20:19,970
I'm useless.

500
00:20:19,970 --> 00:20:20,640
Are you okay?

501
00:20:20,850 --> 00:20:22,150
I'm useless, Gu Nian.

502
00:20:23,200 --> 00:20:24,490
You don't believe me.

503
00:20:24,800 --> 00:20:26,920
I can't change your life,

504
00:20:27,310 --> 00:20:29,820
and I can't sever the fate between you and Feng Huanan.

505
00:20:33,110 --> 00:20:35,400
I came back desperately from the future

506
00:20:36,360 --> 00:20:37,680
to tell you that

507
00:20:38,120 --> 00:20:40,360
Feng Huanan is definitely not a good match for you.

508
00:20:43,530 --> 00:20:46,460
Gu Nian, I know you like Feng Huanan.

509
00:20:47,180 --> 00:20:49,260
But if you can live selfishly for once,

510
00:20:50,360 --> 00:20:53,120
I hope

511
00:20:54,360 --> 00:20:56,510
you'll choose someone who loves you.

512
00:20:56,540 --> 00:20:57,140
Gu Nian.

513
00:21:00,880 --> 00:21:01,680
Gu Nian,

514
00:21:02,330 --> 00:21:03,410
after I leave,

515
00:21:03,880 --> 00:21:05,350
you must stay away from Feng Huanan.

516
00:21:06,060 --> 00:21:07,950
Don't participate in any activities with him.

517
00:21:08,980 --> 00:21:11,060
Staying away from him is loving yourself.

518
00:21:12,340 --> 00:21:13,380
He really can't make it.

519
00:21:14,090 --> 00:21:14,760
Wait a moment.

520
00:21:26,680 --> 00:21:28,290
Your acting is so fake.

521
00:21:28,690 --> 00:21:29,780
She believed it.

522
00:21:51,360 --> 00:21:53,320
Gu Nian, after I leave,

523
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:55,890
you must listen to Lin Xi.

524
00:21:55,890 --> 00:21:56,770
I'm back. Here.

525
00:21:56,930 --> 00:21:57,540
Drink it.

526
00:22:02,600 --> 00:22:03,550
What kind of water is this?

527
00:22:03,760 --> 00:22:04,750
Dishwashing liquid water.

528
00:22:04,880 --> 00:22:06,370
You need to throw up the pills you took.

529
00:22:06,390 --> 00:22:08,110
If you die, how are we going to talk?

530
00:22:08,580 --> 00:22:09,380
Hurry up and drink.

531
00:22:17,900 --> 00:22:19,500
You're really trying to kill yourself?

532
00:22:21,110 --> 00:22:21,940
Not bad, huh?

533
00:22:22,760 --> 00:22:24,560
Lin Xi, what did you tell me?

534
00:22:24,580 --> 00:22:26,830
You said he followed you home and then,

535
00:22:26,860 --> 00:22:28,460
when his threats didn't work, he threatened to commit suicide.

536
00:22:28,630 --> 00:22:30,090
You two are quite good at making up stories.

537
00:22:32,980 --> 00:22:34,780
I should be the one playing along with your act...

538
00:22:34,910 --> 00:22:35,690
Stop.

539
00:22:36,680 --> 00:22:38,520
As expected of a clever medical student like you.

540
00:22:38,650 --> 00:22:40,290
You thought of using vitamins as sleeping pills.

541
00:22:40,330 --> 00:22:41,490
Impressive.

542
00:22:41,800 --> 00:22:43,070
You really went all out with the act.

543
00:22:43,550 --> 00:22:44,500
What's in your mouth?

544
00:22:45,440 --> 00:22:45,990
Toothpaste foam.

545
00:22:46,210 --> 00:22:47,440
I was afraid you'd smell it,

546
00:22:47,440 --> 00:22:48,440
so I didn't even dare to use the mint-flavored one.

547
00:22:48,680 --> 00:22:50,080
Pretty meticulous.

548
00:22:50,100 --> 00:22:52,290
Enough. Stop being so harsh on Lin Xi.

549
00:22:52,520 --> 00:22:53,350
It was my idea.

550
00:22:53,370 --> 00:22:54,650
It was his idea to begin with.

551
00:22:54,650 --> 00:22:56,450
I just let him use the place.

552
00:22:57,040 --> 00:22:58,290
Come on, you really forced water down my throat?

553
00:22:58,290 --> 00:22:59,470
What if you had ended up drowning me?

554
00:23:02,520 --> 00:23:04,200
How did you figure it out?

555
00:23:04,230 --> 00:23:05,640
You're a doctor.

556
00:23:05,740 --> 00:23:07,580
He was very logical just now.

557
00:23:08,590 --> 00:23:09,350
And...

558
00:23:09,370 --> 00:23:11,190
-who would try to commit suicide wearing slippers?
-Who would try to commit suicide wearing slippers?

559
00:23:11,410 --> 00:23:12,640
You know it and you still wore them?

560
00:23:14,040 --> 00:23:15,510
Put away that creepy look of yours.

561
00:23:15,650 --> 00:23:17,810
Tell me, how did you deceive Lin Xi?

562
00:23:19,320 --> 00:23:19,880
Get up.

563
00:23:19,910 --> 00:23:20,670
Nian, stop hitting him!

